---
import Verdant from "../layouts/Verdant.astro";
import Footer from "../components/verdant/Footer";
import { brand } from "../data/verdant";

const updated = "June 2026";
---

<Verdant title="Terms of Service — Verdant" description="Verdant Studio terms of service">
  <!-- ── HERO — Simple, left-pinned ── -->
  <section class="ve-hero">
    <div class="v-wrap ve-hero-inner">
      <p class="v-label">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="v-display ve-hero-head">
        Terms of <span style="color: var(--leaf);">Service</span>.
      </h1>
      <p class="ve-hero-sub">
        Honest terms that cover your rights, Garden's limits, and how your data stays yours. Last updated {updated}.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── TERMS CONTENT ── -->
  <section class="ve-terms-section ve-sec">
    <span class="vh-num" aria-hidden="true">01</span>
    <div class="ve-terms-content">
      <h2>1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
      <p>
        By accessing and using Garden, Verdant Studio products, or any services provided by Verdant ("Services"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, you may not use the Services. These terms apply to all users, whether you are in beta testing or using production features.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Beta Status and "As-Is" Provision</h2>
      <p>
        Garden is currently in Early Access (beta). During beta, the Service, features, functionality, pricing, and availability may change at any time without notice. We are testing and iterating. Beta features are provided "as is" and "as available" without warranty of any kind. We ask for your patience, feedback, and understanding that instability, data loss, or service interruptions may occur. <!-- LEGAL REVIEW: Beta warranty disclaimer scope -->
      </p>

      <h2>3. Your Data and Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Your financial data belongs to you. We do not sell, trade, share, or rent your data to any third party. See our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for a complete description of what data Garden collects, how it is stored, and what never leaves your device. You may export your data at any time in JSON format. You may delete your account and all associated data by contacting us at <a href={`mailto:${brand.email}`}>{brand.email}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>4. User Accounts and Registration</h2>
      <p>
        You may use Garden without creating an account (manual entry and local-only features require no sign-up). If you choose to connect features that require authentication (Grove AI, future bank links), you agree to provide accurate information and to keep your credentials secure. You are responsible for all activity under your credentials. <!-- LEGAL REVIEW: Account liability limits -->
      </p>

      <h2>5. Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p>
        You agree not to use the Services for any illegal purpose or in violation of any applicable law. You agree not to: (a) harass, threaten, or abuse other users; (b) attempt to gain unauthorized access to the Services or other users' data; (c) reverse-engineer, decompile, or attempt to discover the source code or underlying algorithms; (d) disrupt, overload, or flood the Services with automated requests; (e) use the Services to process data for a third party without our written consent; (f) use the Services to create competing products or services. <!-- LEGAL REVIEW: Non-compete scope and enforceability -->
      </p>

      <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        You retain all intellectual property rights to the financial data you enter. Verdant retains all intellectual property rights to the Services, software, design, and brand assets. Your license to use the Services is non-exclusive, non-transferable, and revocable. You may not license, sell, rent, or transfer the Services to any third party.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Disclaimers and Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        <!-- LEGAL REVIEW: Liability caps, warranty disclaimers, and scope of damages -->
        To the fullest extent permitted by applicable law:
        <br /><br />
        (a) The Services are provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind, express or implied. Verdant disclaims all warranties including merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.
        <br /><br />
        (b) Verdant is not liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, punitive, or exemplary damages, including lost profits, data loss, or business interruption—even if advised of the possibility.
        <br /><br />
        (c) Verdant is not liable for the accuracy, completeness, or timeliness of any financial data you enter or import.
        <br /><br />
        (d) Grove AI is not financial, legal, or tax advice. Nothing Grove generates should be treated as professional advice. Verify important decisions with a qualified professional.
        <br /><br />
        (e) You use the Services at your own risk. Verdant is not responsible for data loss, device loss, or theft.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Indemnification</h2>
      <p>
        You agree to indemnify and hold harmless Verdant, its affiliates, and their officers, employees, and agents from any claims, damages, or costs arising from your use of the Services, your violation of these terms, or your violation of any applicable law or third-party rights. <!-- LEGAL REVIEW: Indemnification scope and exclusions -->
      </p>

      <h2>9. Termination</h2>
      <p>
        Verdant may suspend or terminate your access to the Services at any time if you violate these terms, engage in illegal activity, or pose a security risk. You may close your account at any time by contacting <a href={`mailto:${brand.email}`}>{brand.email}</a>. Upon termination, your data remains your property. We will provide you a JSON export within 30 days of your request. If Verdant ceases operations, we will notify you and provide a data export window. <!-- LEGAL REVIEW: Data retention post-termination and company wind-down -->
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes to Terms and Services</h2>
      <p>
        Verdant may update these Terms at any time. If we make material changes, we will notify you by email (if you have provided one) or by posting a notice in the Services. Continued use of the Services after a notice of material change constitutes acceptance of the updated terms. Your only remedy if you object to new terms is to stop using the Services.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Governing Law and Dispute Resolution</h2>
      <p>
        <!-- LEGAL REVIEW: Jurisdiction, governing law, and dispute resolution mechanism -->
        These Terms are governed by applicable law. Any dispute arising from these Terms or your use of the Services shall be resolved according to the procedures outlined below. If you have a dispute with Verdant, you agree to first attempt to resolve it informally by contacting us at <a href={`mailto:${brand.email}`}>{brand.email}</a> within 30 days of the dispute arising.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Third-Party Services and Links</h2>
      <p>
        The Services may contain links to third-party websites or services (e.g., bank providers, financial data aggregators). Verdant is not responsible for the content, privacy practices, or availability of third-party services. Your use of third-party services is governed by their terms and privacy policies. <!-- LEGAL REVIEW: Third-party liability and disclaimers -->
      </p>

      <h2>13. Severability</h2>
      <p>
        If any provision of these Terms is found to be invalid or unenforceable, that provision shall be severed, and the remaining provisions shall remain in full force and effect.
      </p>

      <h2>14. Entire Agreement</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms, together with our Privacy Policy, constitute the entire agreement between you and Verdant regarding the Services. If there is a conflict between these Terms and the Privacy Policy, the Privacy Policy controls with respect to data practices.
      </p>

      <h2>15. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about these Terms, your data, or your rights, please contact us at <a href={`mailto:${brand.email}`}>{brand.email}</a>. We will respond within 7 business days.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); color: var(--moss); font-size: var(--text-sm);">
        {brand.name} — independent, privacy-first software.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer client:visible />
</Verdant>

<style is:global>
  /* ── Terms section ── */
  .ve-terms-section { background: var(--paper-soft); padding-block: clamp(110px, 18vh, 220px); }
  .ve-terms-content { grid-column: 2 / 11; }
  .ve-terms-content h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: var(--text-xl); color: var(--ink); line-height: 1.3; margin: 2rem 0 0.8rem 0; font-weight: 400; }
  .ve-terms-content h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .ve-terms-content p { font-size: var(--text-lg); line-height: 1.7; color: var(--ink-soft); max-width: 70ch; margin-bottom: 1.6rem; }
  .ve-terms-content a { color: var(--leaf); text-decoration: none; }
  .ve-terms-content a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  /* ── Responsive ── */
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .ve-hero-bg { display: none; }
    .ve-hero-inner { grid-column: 1 / 13; }
    .ve-terms-content { grid-column: 1 / 13; }
  }
</style>
